;TEICOPLANIN IS A FAMILY OF TETRACYCLIC GLYCOPEPTIDE ANTIBIOTICS. THE SCAFFOLD IS A HEPTAPEPTIDE FURTHER GLYCOSYLATED BY THREE MONO SACCHARIDES: MANNOSE, N-ACETYLGLUCOSAMINE AND BETA-D-GLUCOSAMINE AND ONLY DIFFER BY THE SIDE CHAIN ATTACHED TO THE LATTER. TEICOPLANIN A2-2 HAS 8-METHYLNONANOIC ACID ATTACHED TO GLUCOSAMINE.
